        "timestamp": "2021-09-07 07:30:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2\n\nsth is terribly bad here if you need a change like this.\nIt's either me who wrote a terrible code or some bad use case for it which was not taken into account while designing this\nCould you please explain exactly what is your use case in which the current implementation fails?\n\n-2 just to make sure that we hold it back as I expect it may cause number of serious issues taken into account how much we use mariadb",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e829c07981dad01bc3d5fa8b322f0220e7557a32",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5315,
          "name": "Mahmoud Abdelhamid",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mahmoud.abdelhamid@orange.com",
          "username": "mhamid"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-09-07 12:26:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2\n> \n> sth is terribly bad here if you need a change like this.\n> It's either me who wrote a terrible code or some bad use case for it which was not taken into account while designing this\n> Could you please explain exactly what is your use case in which the current implementation fails?\n> \n> -2 just to make sure that we hold it back as I expect it may cause number of serious issues taken into account how much we use mariadb\n\nHello Krzysztof,\n\nThanks for review and comment, I agree this isn't the best solution, but let me describe why I proposed such change (a verbal discussion can save much time, drop me a message on slack if needed):\n\n1st- Mariadb-init project was designed such that it will only initiate the common mariadb-galera DB. But due to the fact that \"something\" should initiate local DB as well (if we have db_cmd.sh like VID and local cluster is needed), that is to say mariadb-init will be used to initiate either local or the common DB. \n\n2nd- I have checked all charts and found that (common.mariadbSecret) not used anywhere, that is why i assumed it wasn't tested properly (I faced same issue with common.mariadbService and common.mariadbPort which I updated both previously). \nFor example (vid) used (common.secret.envFromSecretFast) to get DB credentials not (common.mariadbSecret).\n\n3rd- The use case I have difficulty with, is the charts those have many components (e.g. CDS and Policy). Since we need all components to use the same DB, then we have to create and initiate the DB on the parent component and pass DB info (host, port, credentials) to each of the components.\n\nOkay, here comes the tricky part (take \"CDS\" and its component \"cds-blueprints-processor\" as example):\n\n- According to parent values file, CDS will create secret named (RELEASE-cds-db-secret)\n- Using (common.mariadbSecet) template in cds-blueprints-processor deployment:\n\n{{- define \"common.mariadbSecret\" -}}\n  {{- if .Values.global.mariadbGalera.localCluster -}} \n    {{ printf \"%s-%s-db-user-credentials\" (include \"common.fullname\" .) (index .Values \"mariadb-galera\" \"nameOverride\") -}}\n  {{- else -}}\n    {{ printf \"%s-%s-%s\" ( include \"common.release\" .) (index .Values \"mariadb-init\" \"nameOverride\") (index .Values \"mariadb-init\" \"config\" \"mysqlDatabase\" ) -}}\n  {{- end -}}\n{{- end -}}\n\nThis will result into:\n- If local cluster is enabled, (common.mariadbSecret) will be (RELEASE-cds-blueprints-processor-sdnctl), which isn't found since the created secret on the parent component is (RELEASE-cds-db-secret).\n- If common DB will be used (by default), (common.mariadbSecret) will be (RELEASE-cds-mariadb-init-sdnctl), which isn't found as mariadb-init chart won't create any secrets since it used (userCredentialsExternalSecret = RELEASE-cds-db-secret).\n\nIn both cases build will fail.\n\nWhat I am trying to do is to pass the created secret name (RELEASE-cds-db-secret) on the parent chart to its components using (mariadb-init.userCredentialsExternalSecret) parameter.\n\nOther suggestion, \n- Remove (common.mariadbSecret) entirely and use (envFromSecretFast) with static secret UID from parent chart.\n- No secrets got created on the chart, pass the username to mariadb-init which by turn generate a secret according to predefined naming convention and use (common.mariadbSecret) to retrieve it. \nKindly note there won't be a need for the condition if local cluster or not as it should be same secret.\n\nIf you have better options lets discuss it.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
